        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 3:59PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southwest of Aguilares, or 21 miles southeast of Laredo, moving
east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oilton, Mirando City, and Aguilares.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
